<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN266">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>payaṅkeḻu māmaḻai peyyātu māṟik</l>
<l>kayaṅkaḷi muḷiyuṅ kōṭai yāyiṉum</l>
<l>puḻaṟkā lāmpa lakalaṭai nīḻaṟ</l>
<l>katirkōṭu nantiṉ curimuka vēṟṟai</l>
<l>nākiḷa vaḷaiyoṭu pakaṉmaṇam pukūu</l>
<l>nīrtikaḻ kaḻaṉi nāṭukeḻu peruviṟal</l>
<l>vāṉṟōy nīḷkuṭai vayamāṉ ceṉṉi</l>
<l>cāṉṟō rirunta vavaiyat tuṟṟō</l>
<l>ṉācā keṉṉum pūcal pōla</l>
<l>vallē kaḷaimati yattai yuḷḷiya</l>
<l>viruntukaṇ ṭoḷikkun tiruntā vāḻkkaip</l>
<l>poṟippuṇa ruṭampiṟ ṟōṉṟiyeṉ</l>
<l>ṉaṟivukeṭa niṉṟa nalkūr maiyē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>With great victories over lands with water-glittering paddy fields, (6)</l>
<l>where the curly-faced male snail with ear[-shaped] feelers (4)</l>
<l>enters into daytime union with the young sea-snail conch (5)</l>
<l>in the shade of the wide leaves of tube-stemmed white waterlilies (3)</l>
<l>even though the west wind dries the silt by the pond (2) </l>
<l>after the well-filled dark clouds changed [position] without raining, (1)</l>
<l>Oh top [man] on the strong animal with a sky-touchig tall parasol (7),</l>
<l>resembling the clamour that says “may he be a support, (9)</l>
<l>to the one who experiences [his] assembly where worthy men sit”, (8)</l>
<l>may you remove [it] fast (10a-c)</l>
<l>– the poverty that lasted so that my knowledge got lost, (13)</l>
<l>appearing with a body joined with the marks (12)</l>
<l>of an imperfect living that will hide when seeing the feasts remembered. (10d-11)</l>
</lg>
    </div>
